                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="rubrication" xml:id="d1">
                        <p>Executed in the main hand; starting from fol. <locus target="#6v"/>some rubricated elements (e.g., dots in the punctuation signs and numerals, lines marking runovers, letters, names and words on fols. <locus from="123r" to="130r"/>) are executed in a different hand, in vivid orange ink </p>
                        <!--Executed in the main hand; starting from fol. 6v, some rubricated elements (e.g., dots in the punctuation signs and numerals, lines marking runovers, letters, names and words on fols. 123r-130r) are executed in a different hand, in vivid orange ink -->
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="ordering" xml:id="d2">
                        <p>Undecorated quire marks are written in the left upper corner of the first leaf of the quire.</p>
                        <!--Undecorated quire marks are written in the left upper corner of the first leaf of the quire.-->
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>- Images on fols. <locus from="1v" to="2r"/> depicting the donor and King David playing the harp. The legend is written in several hands: በቅዱስ᎓ዳዊት᎓ተማኅፀንኩ᎓ተስፋ᎓ሚካኤል᎓&lt;…&gt; ገብረ᎓ኢየሱስ“I entrust myself to Saint David. Täsfa Mikaˀel, … Gäbrä ˀIyäsus”. One more name was erased </p>
                        <p>- Each unit of ten Psalms is preceded by an elaborate coloured ornamental band on fols. <locus target="#3r"/>(unfinished); <locus target="#9r"/>(missing on fol. <locus target="#12v"/>before Ps. <locus target="#21"/>), <locus target="#21v #29v #36r #41r #48r #57v #64v #69v #80r #90v #93r #99r"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- Blind tooled decoration on the leather cover of the front and back boards consist of a cross, four squares beneath and frames with geometric pattern. The ornament is poorly visible. Leather turn-ins and doublures are decorated with tooled circles and crosses in squares.</p>
                        <!--- Images on fols. 1v-2r depicting the donor and King David playing the harp. The legend is written in several hands: በቅዱስ᎓ዳዊት᎓ተማኅፀንኩ᎓ተስፋ᎓ሚካኤል᎓<…> ገብረ᎓ኢየሱስ“I entrust myself to Saint David. Täsfa Mikaˀel, … Gäbrä ˀIyäsus”. One more name was erased  - Each unit of ten Psalms is preceded by an elaborate coloured ornamental band on fols. 3r (unfinished); 9r, (missing on fol. 12v, before Ps. 21), 21v, 29v, 36r, 41r, 48r, 57v, 64v, 69v, 80r, 90v, 93r, 99r  - Blind tooled decoration on the leather cover of the front and back boards consist of a cross, four squares beneath and frames with geometric pattern. The ornament is poorly visible. Leather turn-ins and doublures are decorated with tooled circles and crosses in squares.-->
                     </decoNote>
