                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>Ethiopian binding. Two wooden boards covered with reddish brown tooled leather; patched leather doublures. </p>
                           <p>Two pairs of sewing stations. </p>
                           <p>Endbands are missing. </p>
                           <p>A small square recession on the inner sides of the front and back boards could have been used for small mirrors or devotional pictures. </p>
                           <p>Kept in the traditional two-part slip case made of thick leather, repaired with modern cords. </p>
