                  <p>The names of the commissionersor owners might be Täsfa Mikaˀel and Gäbrä ˀIyäsus (fol. <locus target="#1v"/>). Another hint to the owner might appear on fol. <locus target="#121v"/>where the name “Wäldä Mikaˀel from the land of Goǧǧam” is crudely written. One more name (yaläm sǝm, “secular name”), Märša Yǝmär, is mentioned on fol. <locus target="#130vb"/>and the female name Wälättä Maryam is written in the top margin of fol. <locus target="#122r"/>. </p>
